{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/QuickStart","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Getting started","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService"],"anchor":"Getting-started"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"1-Add-the-SDK","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"1. Add the SDK"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"YEOFR","type":"text"}]},{"text":" Swift package","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https:\/\/github.com\/YEOMessaging\/YEOFR-SPM"},{"type":"text","text":") to your project, pinned to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"exact version ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.7.3","type":"text"}]},{"text":", then ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"import YEOFR"},{"type":"text","text":". The binary is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"arm64","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"device-only","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — it does not run on the simulator.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"2. Pilot unlock for non-YEO bundle IDs","anchor":"2-Pilot-unlock-for-non-YEO-bundle-IDs"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"YEOFR is gated to YEO-owned apps by default; a non-YEO bundle id aborts on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"construction. Evaluation customers get a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"temporary unlock code","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bypasses the gate during a fixed pilot window — email","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"christo@yeomessaging.com","type":"text"}]},{"text":" to request one. Pass it to the initializer","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(step 3). YEO-owned apps pass the gate natively.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"3. Drive everything with `FaceTrustService`","anchor":"3-Drive-everything-with-FaceTrustService","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is the turnkey entry point. It owns the engine, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"camera, the fused-trust pipeline (face recognition + liveness CNN +"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"TrueDepth), the identity gate, and tracker persistence, and exposes two"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"streams: one for live trust verdicts and one for guided enrolment."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import YEOFR","","let service = FaceTrustService(pilotUnlockCode: \"YOUR-PILOT-CODE\")","","\/\/ Attach the preview to an AVCaptureVideoPreviewLayer:","\/\/   previewLayer.session = service.previewSession","","try await service.start()    \/\/ warm-up, restore enrolment, arm gate, start camera"]},{"text":"4. Enrol a face","anchor":"4-Enrol-a-face","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enroll(name:)"},{"type":"text","text":" runs a short guided capture, persists the gallery, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"re-arms the identity gate. Iterate the returned stream to coach the user:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["for await step in service.enroll(name: \"Alice\") {","    switch step.phase {","    case .capturing: show(step.prompt, progress: step.poseProgress)","    case .completed: dismiss()","    case .failed:    show(step.prompt)","    @unknown default: break","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A single front pose is enough to separate the enrolled user from other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"people. Pass "},{"code":"poses: PoseTarget.lightingAwareGallerySequence","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capture off-axis poses + a lighting pass, which improves recall as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"user turns their head."}]},{"anchor":"5-Run-live-recognition","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"5. Run live recognition"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["for await update in service.updates() {","    switch update.status {","    case .trusted:    badge(\"TRUSTED — \\(update.matchedName ?? \"\")\", .green)","    case .notTrusted: badge(\"NOT TRUSTED\", .red)","    case .badFraming: badge(\"ADJUST FRAMING\", .orange)","    case .noFace:     badge(\"NO FACE\", .gray)","    @unknown default: break","    }","    \/\/ update.livenessGenuine \/ update.depthIsThreeD are the contributing signals.","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"update.status == .trusted"},{"type":"text","text":" already fuses face recognition, liveness, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"TrueDepth, with framing applied — you never pick a similarity threshold,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and you never touch the identity gate (forgetting it would collapse trust"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to liveness + depth, so any live face would pass). The enrolled gallery is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"saved across launches automatically; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"service.enrolledName"},{"type":"text","text":" reflects who is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"enrolled."}]},{"text":"See also","anchor":"See-also","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A complete, runnable SwiftUI app lives in the package’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/FRPilot"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService"},{"type":"text","text":" — full API."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustUpdate"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/EnrollmentProgress"},{"type":"text","text":" — the stream payloads."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Recognise the enrolled user and reject everyone else, in a few lines."}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"QuickStart","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"YEOFR"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/yeofr\/quickstart"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["\/documentation\/yeofr\/quickstart"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"references":{"doc://com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR":{"url":"\/documentation\/yeofr","title":"YEOFR","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"On-device face recognition with fused liveness and TrueDepth anti-spoofing."}],"type":"topic"},"doc://com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/FaceTrustUpdate":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"One per-frame trust readout, with the framing gate already applied — so the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consumer renders a state, not a fusion of raw signals. Yielded by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService\/updates()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"FaceTrustUpdate"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustUpdate","title":"FaceTrustUpdate","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"FaceTrustUpdate"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr\/facetrustupdate"},"doc://com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/FaceTrustService/enroll(name:poses:)":{"abstract":[{"text":"Enrol ","type":"text"},{"code":"name","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from the live camera and return a stream of capture","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"progress. The existing frame loop drives the gallery walk; on completion","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the service persists the gallery, refreshes ","type":"text"},{"code":"enrolledName","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", resets the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"trust pipeline against the fresh gallery, and re-arms the identity gate —","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the consumer does none of that.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enroll"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"name"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"poses"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:5YEOFR10PoseTargetO","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PoseTarget"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"AsyncStream"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:5YEOFR18EnrollmentProgressV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnrollmentProgress"},{"kind":"t